   "description": "Olof Valter Elofson was a high school teacher in Mariestad. He was born on June 20th, 1911 in Uppsala, to Dr. Phil. h.c. Anders E. and Käthe Schmidt. He completed his secondary school education from Uppsala University in 1930. He went on to receive a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1934, a Master of Arts degree in 1938, a Licentiate of Philosophy degree in 1938, and a Doctorate of Philosophy degree in 1941, all from Uppsala University. He also completed a teaching internship in Uppsala from 1942-1943. He was a subject teacher in Vilhelmina from 1941-1942, a substitute teacher in Hässleholm from 1943-1945, an acting teacher there from 1945-1946, and then a teacher at Mariestad’s coeducational secondary school from 1946-1947. In addition to his regular teaching duties, he taught hourly lessons at various institutions. Olof was an avid traveler, and visited several countries including Norway, Germany, Portugal, Spain, North Africa, Italy, Yugoslavia, Switzerland, England, France, Hungary, the Balkans, Turkey, and the Soviet Union. Some of his written works relate to marine ostracods, birds, and other related subjects."
